-- Central Glass Rises on Plan to Make Lithium-Ion Battery Materials in China
-- B y   K y u n g   B o k   C h o
-- 2010-10-14T00:11:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/central-glass-rises-on-plan-to-make-lithium-ion-battery-materials-in-china.html
Central Glass Co., a Japanese
glassmaker, rose the most in eight months in Tokyo trading after
saying it will form a venture in China to produce a material
used in lithium-ion batteries.  Central Glass gained 5.2 percent to 367 yen as of 9:09 a.m.
on the Tokyo Stock Exchange, headed for the biggest advance
since Feb. 16. The benchmark Topix index climbed 0.9 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kyung Bok Cho at 
 kcho7@bloomberg.net  